WGU C195

-Appointment Scheduling and Management Application-
This application allows users to create, modify, and delete appointments and affiliated customers, as well as view summary reports regarding the schedule.

Author - Dustin Waite
Contact Information - dwaite8@wgu.edu
Student Application Version - v1.0
Date - 2/14/2023
IDE - IntelliJ IDEA Community Edition 2021.1.3
JavaFX - Javafx-sdk-17.0.1
MySQL - mysql-connector-java-8.0.25
JDK - openjfx-11.0.2_windows-x64_bin-sdk

-Application Instructions-

upon opening the program you will be greeted with a login screen where you enter a username and password stored in the database.

if the fields are correct you will be directed to the main menu with three options.
-customer screen
-appointments screen
-reports screen

there is an alert at the bottom of the window that indicates if the user has a upcoming appointment within the the next 15 minutes.

-customer screen-
*here you can add, update, or delete any customer data.
*pressing the start create button will generate a random customer id in order to insert new data into database.
*upon customer deletion all related appointments will be deleted as well after an alert.
*customers can be filtered by country and first level divisions combo box.

-appointments screen-
*the user can add, update, or delete appointments.
*the appointments can by organized by month, week, or all by selecting the radio buttons.
*by selecting an appointment in the table, the users info will populate into relative fields and be updatable.
*the start create will clear all fields including customer_ID in order to insert appointment after pressing the save button.

-reports screen-
*the user can populate a table by contact, and see a contacts schedule and
includes appointment ID, title, type and description, start date and time, end date and time, and customer ID.
*the user can display the total amount of appointments by type, month, or location by selected associated combo box.